      <hedline>
        <hl1>Fed Up With Spam, and Fighting Back</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Paul Nordberg letter says junk e-mail should be taxed (Feb 1 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>There is a simple and effective way of dealing with junk e-mail: tax it. The revenues would easily finance the war on terrorism, ensure the future of Social Security and cover the expenses of reversing global warming.</p>
        <p>Paul Nordberg  Ipswich, Mass., Feb. 1, 2005</p>
      </block>
